' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' INTERFACE REALIZATIONS  (..|>)  &  USAGE DEPENDENCIES  (..>)
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

' Anti-Corruption Layer realises every Unity-touching interface
"SteamVRInputAdapter"        ..|> "IInputProvider"
"SteamVRInputAdapter"        ..|> "IPointer"
"SteamVRInputAdapter"        ..|> "IGripInput"
"SteamVRInputAdapter"        ..|> "IHaptics"
"UnityInputSystemAdapter"    ..|> "IInputProvider"
"UnityKeywordRecogniserAdapter" ..|> "IVoiceRecogniser"
"RenderPipelineAdapter"      ..|> "IRenderPipeline"

' Server-side gateway realises the Client Service Contract
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "IVolumeLoader"
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "ICoordinateSystem"
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "IStatisticsService"
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "ITextureFactory"
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "IMaskEditor"
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "IDataExporter"
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "IFeatureCatalogClient"
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     ..|> "IWorkspaceStoreClient"

' Client gateway is the proxy that consumes the contract
"ServiceGatewayClient"       ..> "IVolumeLoader"          : proxies
"ServiceGatewayClient"       ..> "IFeatureCatalogClient"  : proxies
"ServiceGatewayClient"       ..> "IWorkspaceStoreClient"  : proxies

' Plug-ins realise the versioned C ABI
"fits-reader"   ..|> "IPluginABI"
"fits-writer"   ..|> "IPluginABI"
"votable"       ..|> "IPluginABI"
"tiff"          ..|> "IPluginABI"
"wcs-transform" ..|> "IPluginABI"
"statistics"    ..|> "IPluginABI"
"downsampler"   ..|> "IPluginABI"
"source-finder" ..|> "IPluginABI"

' Plug-ins wrap third-party libs
"fits-reader"   --> "CFITSIO"            : DllImport
"fits-writer"   --> "CFITSIO"            : DllImport
"votable"       --> "CFITSIO"            : DllImport
"wcs-transform" --> "StarlinkAST"        : DllImport
"statistics"    --> "cminpack + OpenMP"  : DllImport
"downsampler"   --> "cminpack + OpenMP"  : DllImport
"source-finder" --> "cminpack + OpenMP"  : DllImport

' Use cases reach the plug-in host through the registry
"LoadFitsCubeUseCase"      ..> "PluginRegistry" : resolve "fits-reader"
"RequestSubcubeUseCase"    ..> "PluginRegistry" : resolve "downsampler"
"ExportMaskUseCase"        ..> "PluginRegistry" : resolve "fits-writer"
"ComputeStatisticsUseCase" ..> "PluginRegistry" : resolve "statistics"
"FeatureSetService"        ..> "PluginRegistry" : resolve "source-finder"
"LoadFitsCubeUseCase"      ..> "PluginRegistry" : resolve "wcs-transform"

' Downward layer dependencies (Application → Domain;
'                              Infra → Application/Domain;
'                              PluginHost is the lowest level)
"ServiceGatewayEndpoint"     --> "ApplicationLayer" : dispatch
"LoadFitsCubeUseCase"        --> "VolumeDataSet"
"RequestSubcubeUseCase"      --> "VolumeDataSet"
"ExportMaskUseCase"          --> "VolumeDataSet"
"ComputeStatisticsUseCase"   --> "VolumeDataSet"
"PaintMaskUseCase"           --> "Mask"
"FeatureSetService"          --> "FeatureCatalog"
"WorkspaceService"           --> "Workspace"
"WorkspaceRepository"        ..> "Workspace"        : persists
"FeatureCatalogRepository"   ..> "FeatureCatalog"   : persists

' Client subsystems consume the gateway, never the server directly
"DesktopGuiSubsystem"   ..> "ServiceGatewayClient" : uses
"VRRenderingSubsystem"  ..> "ServiceGatewayClient" : uses
"VRInteractionSubsystem" ..> "ServiceGatewayClient" : uses

' Transport carries the gateway traffic
"ServiceGatewayClient"   --> "Transport"               : sends
"Transport"              --> "ServiceGatewayEndpoint"  : delivers

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' Hidden layout hints — strictly vertical flow:
'   Client → Transport → Server → Plug-ins → Libs
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
"iDaVIEClient"        -[hidden]down- "Transport"
"Transport"           -[hidden]down- "iDaVIEServer"
"iDaVIEServer"        -[hidden]down- "IPluginABI"
"IPluginABI"          -[hidden]down- "fits-reader"
"fits-reader"         -[hidden]down- "CFITSIO"
"wcs-transform"       -[hidden]down- "StarlinkAST"

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' Architectural-rationale notes
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

note right of "iDaVIESystem"
  **Spec §4 — Target style**
  • Client–server at system level (this BDD).
  • Micro-kernel server with versioned C ABI.
  • Strict downward layering inside the kernel:
    Domain → Application → Infrastructure → Plug-in Host.
  • Anti-Corruption Layer wraps all Unity 6 /
    SteamVR / URP / HDRP / UI Toolkit types.
end note

note right of "Transport"
  **ADR-001 — Transport contract**
  • Local: JSON-RPC over named pipe.
  • Remote: gRPC over TCP/TLS.
  • The ServiceGateway is the **only** seam
    crossing the client/server boundary.
end note

note bottom of "IPluginABI"
  **ADR-002 / 003 / 004 / 005 — Plug-in C ABI**
  • Semver-versioned; ABI-stable within a major.
  • Structured error model (status codes + context).
  • Kernel-owned threads; plug-ins must be re-entrant.
  • Memory ownership: caller allocates output buffers,
    callee fills; lifetime tokens for streaming results.
end note

note right of "DomainLayer"
  **Spec §4.2.3 — Domain Unity-free**
  Only the Anti-Corruption Layer and the three
  Unity-side adapters (Visualisers, View,
  MonoBehaviour bridges) may import UnityEngine /
  SteamVR / URP / HDRP. Enforced by NDepend CQLinq
  in CI (ADR-006).
end note

note right of "PluginHost"
  **Spec §6.1, ADR-008 — Service Locator**
  PluginRegistry is the **only** Service Locator
  in the system; everywhere else inside the kernel
  uses constructor injection.
  GRASP: Indirection + Protected Variations.
end note

note left of "Feature"
  **Spec §6.5 — Sub-team 5**
  Feature is a first-class domain aggregate.
  Three flavours (Masked, Imported, UserDefined)
  substitutable behind one IFeature interface (LSP).
  Statistics are GRASP Information-Expert methods
  on the aggregate itself.
end note

note left of "Workspace"
  **Spec §6.7 — Sub-team 7**
  Workspace owns the lifecycle of a user session.
  State contracts with every other sub-team are
  signed off by the Architecture Guild on Day 9.
end note

@enduml
